analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Consolidation persists amid volatility expansion. The GMS equilibrium at 50 necessitates tactical neutrality as volatility expansion disrupts equity momentum. Despite credit spread compression, the divergence between crude appreciation and copper contraction signals cyclical friction. Persistent real interest rates and a burgeoning VIX threshold indicate localized regime degradation, neutralizing fiscal-monetary nexus benefits until the OGV vector transcends its flat trajectory. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
